{{Infobox baseball biography |name=Kook Hae-seong |image= |image_size= |team=Doosan Bears |number=15 |position=[[Outfielder]] |birth_date={{birth date and age|1989|12|8}} |birth_place=[[Gunsan]] |bats=Switch |throws=Right |debutleague=[[KBO League|KBO]] |debutdate= |debutyear=2012 |debutteam=Doosan Bears |finaldate= |finalyear= |finalteam= |statyear= |statleague= |stat1label= |stat1value= |stat3label= |stat3value= |stat4label= |stat4value= |teams=* [[Doosan Bears]] ({{by|2009}}–present) * [[Korean Police Baseball Team|Police Baseball Team]] (army) ([[2010 in baseball|2009]]&ndash;[[2012 in baseball|2012]]) |highlights=|update=}}
'''Kook Hae-seong''' ({{korean|국해성|鞠海成}}; born 8 December 1989) is a South Korean professional baseball [[outfielder]] who is currently playing for the [[Doosan Bears]] of [[Korea Baseball Organization]]. His major position is [[right fielder]] and [[left fielder]], but he sometimes plays as [[center fielder]] or [[first baseman]]. He graduated from {{ill|Incheon High School|ko|인천고등학교}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.koreabaseball.com/Record/Player/HitterDetail/Basic.aspx?playerId=79290|title=KBO 홈페이지 player infro|last=스포츠투아이|first=|date=|website=|language=ko|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=30 April 2018}}</ref> Upon graduation from high school, he made himself eligible for the 2008 KBO First-Year Player Draft, but went undrafted. Instead, Kook signed a contract with the [[Chicago Cubs]] in 2007. However, after the problem of elbow was found and the contract was broken, he was signed by the Doosan Bears as an undrafted free agent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spotvnews.co.kr/?mod=news&act=articleView&idxno=47708|title='마의 LF' 숙제 얻은 박헌도-국해성|last=|first=|date=2016-03-15|work=SPOTVNEWS|access-date=30 April 2018|language=ko}}</ref>
